\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/mf.siegel.family.sp4z}{The ring of Siegel modular forms of degree 2 with respect to the full modular group}}
\begin{definition}\label{mf.siegel.family.sp4z}
\uses{group.sp2gr,mf.siegel,mf.siegel.degree,mf.siegel.eisenstein_series}
\leanok
By a classical result of Jun-Ichi Igusa \cite{mr:0141643}, the ring $M_{2}({\rm Sp}(4,\mathbb{Z}))$ of \hyperref[mf.siegel]{Siegel modular forms} of \hyperref[mf.siegel.degree]{degree} 2 with *even weights* with respect to 
the \hyperref[group.sp2gr]{full modular group} $\mathrm{Sp}(4,{\Bbb Z})$ is generated by the four algebraically independent \hyperref[mf.siegel.eisenstein_series]{Eisenstein series}: $\psi_4$</a>,  $\psi_6$</a>, $\psi_{10}$</a>, $\psi_{12}$</a>.

Alternatively, $\psi_{10}$ can be replaced by the cusp form
$$\chi_{10} =-43867\cdot 2^{-12}3^{-5}5^{-2}7^{-1}53^{-1}(\psi_4\psi_6-\psi_{10})$$
and $\psi_{12}$ can be replaced by the cusp form
$$\chi_{12}=131\cdot593\cdot2^{-13}3^{-7}5^{-3}7^{-2}337^{-1}(441\psi_4^3+250\psi_6^2-691\psi_{12}).$$

Note that $\chi_{10}$ is a Saito-Kurokawa lifting coming from the cuspform of weight 18 for ${\rm SL}(2,\mathbb{Z})$, and $\chi_{12}$ is a Saito-Kurokawa lifting coming from the cuspform of weight 22.

The even weight forms are:
$${\Bbb C}[\psi_4,\psi_6,\chi_{10},\chi_{12}],$$
with the cusp forms being the ideal generated by $\chi_{10}, \chi_{12}$.

To generate the odd weight forms, there is one more generator, namely
$\chi_{35}$

The odd weight forms are:
$$\chi_{35}\,{\Bbb C}[\psi_4,\psi_6,\chi_{10},\chi_{12}],$$
where $\chi_{35}$ is a weight 35 cusp form.

We write
\begin{itemize}
\item  $A=\psi_4$,
\item  $B=\psi_6$,
\item  $C=-4\chi_{10}$,
\item  $D=12\chi_{12}$,
\end{itemize}
for short in the modular form pages.

\end{definition}


